<article id="node-16952">
<h1 >3.4.8.120 Start Day for Payments Accessed via RAFS</h1>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> THIS SCHEME CLOSED on 31 July 2001 and the following INFORMATION is FOR HISTORICAL PURPOSES ONLY.</p>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>Start day rules for all payments are set out in <a href="../../../8/3">8.3</a>. This topic contains notes and examples on the application of those rules to <a href="../../../acronyms#rafs" title="Retirement assistance for farmers scheme">RAFS</a> cases.</p>
<p>The start date for a RAFS applicant/recipient's payment depends on the date:</p>
<ul><li>that legal transfer of the farm property occurred, under the relevant State land law (<a href="../../../1/1/r/140">1.1.R.140</a>), AND</li>
<li>the farmer or their partner, reaches age pension age, AND</li>
<li>an actual claim is lodged.</li>
</ul><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 23(5A) Pension age</p>
</div>
<h2>Backdating provisions</h2>
<p>Applicants/recipients CANNOT receive backpayment beyond 15 September 1997, when the scheme commenced. If the RAFS claim was lodged in the first year of the scheme's operation, then some backpayment may occur, as explained in the rest of this topic.</p>
<h2>Transfer in the 5 years before the scheme started</h2>
<p>The following table explains the commencement day provisions for applicants/recipients who transferred their farm between 14 September 1992 and 15 September 1997:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">If the qualifying farmer…</th>
<th scope="col">Then their pension…</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>
<ul><li>transferred the farm in the 5 years before the scheme started, AND</li>
<li>claimed under RAFS before 15/9/98,</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>commenced or was reassessed from the LATER of the following dates:</p>
<ul><li>15/9/97, OR</li>
<li>the date they qualify for <a href="../../../acronyms#age" title="Age pension">Age</a>.</li>
</ul><p>The rate of Age for this period should be based on the applicant/recipient and partner's income and assets during the backpayment period, and relevant income details will need to be provided.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>
<ul><li>transferred the farm in the 5 years before the scheme started, AND</li>
<li>FAILED TO CLAIM under RAFS before 15/9/98,</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>commences or is reassessed from the LATER of the following dates:</p>
<ul><li>date of claim, OR</li>
<li>the date they qualify for Age.</li>
</ul></td>
</tr></tbody></table><div class="example">
<p><strong>Example 1:</strong> An applicant/recipient was in paid employment that ceased on 1 June 1998, and they claimed Age on 1 July 1998. Their income from employment will be taken into account when calculating their backpayment for the period 15 September 1997 to 1 July 1998.</p>
</div>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example 2:</strong> An applicant/recipient was receiving pension on 12 November 1997 when they claimed an increase in payment under RAFS. The applicant/recipient's pension is reassessed with effect from 15 September 1997, because the farm is no longer treated as a deprived asset.</p>
</div>
<h2>Transfer &amp; claim in the first year of the scheme</h2>
<p>The following table explains the commencement day provisions for applicants/recipients who transferred their farm and claimed under RAFS, in the period 15 September 1997 to 14 September 1998:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">If the qualifying farmer…</th>
<th scope="col">Then their pension…</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>
<ul><li>transfers the farm before 15/9/98, and</li>
<li>claims under RAFS before that date,</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>is backdated to the LATER of the following dates:</p>
<ul><li>the date that the transfer was completed, or</li>
<li>the date they qualified for Age.</li>
</ul><p>The rate of Age for this period should be based on the applicant/recipient and partner's income and assets during the backpayment period, and relevant income details will need to be provided.</p>
</td>
</tr></tbody></table><div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> A farmer transferred his farm to the eligible descendant on 1 October 1997, and turned 65 on 1 January 1998. If the farmer lodges a claim for Age before 15 September 1998, payment will be backdated to 1 January 1998.</p>
</div>
<h2>Transfer after the first year of the scheme's operation</h2>
<p>The following table explains the backpayment provisions when a farmer transfers the farm after 14 September 1998 but before 30 June 2001:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">If the qualifying farmer…</th>
<th scope="col">Then their pension…</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>claims WITHIN 3 months of the farm being transferred,</td>
<td>is backdated to the later of the following dates:
<ul><li>the date the transfer was completed, OR</li>
<li>the date they qualified for Age.</li>
</ul></td>
</tr><tr><td>claims MORE THAN 3 months after the farm being transferred,</td>
<td>is backdated to the later of the following dates:
<ul><li>the date on which they claim, OR</li>
<li>the date they qualified for Age.</li>
</ul></td>
</tr></tbody></table></article>	<div id="view-last-reviewed-date">
		
		  
